<promed@promedmail.org>
[There is an excellent overall review article with recommendations related
to travel and management of suspected cases during airline travel in this
week's WER accessible at: <http://www.who.int/wer/pdf/2003/wer7814.pdf>.
The WER article also contains the template questionnaire for data
collection on SARS cases to allow for uniform data collection and analyses.
There is an additional information piece on travel advice at
<http://www.who.int/csr/sars/2003_04_04a/en/>
that repeats the advice of 3 Apr 2003, recommending holding off
non-essential travel to China's Guangdong Province and Hong Kong SAR -
