Date: 4 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Eurosurveillance Weekly 4 Apr 2003 Volume 7 Issue 14 [edited]
<http://www.eurosurveillance.org/ew/2003/030403.asp>

SARS: the situation in France - 3 Apr 2003
---------------------------------
Since an epidemic alert was released in France on 13 Mar 2003 (1), 216
people with symptoms of respiratory infection returning from Vietnam,
China, Hong Kong, or Singapore were notified to the national Public Health
Institute (Institut de veille sanitaire, InVS) (2). Of these, 201 were
excluded after clinical, radiological, biological, and epidemiological
evaluation of their compatibility with Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome
(SARS).
As of 3 Apr 2003, 12 patients are still under surveillance. 3 probable
cases of SARS have been identified and are currently hospitalised in
isolation. The first case was a traveller who returned from Hanoi (Vietnam)
on 23 Mar 2003. The date of onset of symptoms of the latter 2 cases was 26
Mar 2003 and 30 Mar 2003, respectively. Their link with other SARS cases is
under investigation.
In France, the health authorities and the ministry of foreign affairs have
advised against travel to Hong Kong and China (Beijing, Guangdong, and
Shanxi provinces) and recommended postponing travel to other affected areas
(3). Travellers returning from Hong Kong, Beijing, Guangdong,and Shanxi
provinces in China, Taiwan, Hanoi, Toronto, and Singapore are asked to fill
in an identification form upon arrival at the international
Charles-de-Gaulle airport in France. A similar surveillance procedure was
implemented for charter flights landing in other airports in France. People
returning from southeast Asia who develop respiratory symptoms with a fever
above 38 C within 10 days of landing are advised to contact the emergency
on-call service, and not to directly consult hospital emergency wards or
their physician.
References :
1. French Health General Directorate press release. (accessed 2 April at
<http://www.sante.gouv.fr/htm/dossiers/pneumapathies/index.htm>)
2. InVS update on the SARS epidemic in 2 April (accessed 2 April at
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=presse/2003/le_point_sur/sras_asie_03
0403>)
3. Advice to travellers, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, (accessed 2 April at
<http://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fcv/etrangers/avis/conseils/fiches/fiche.asp?
onglet=1&pays=VIET%20NAM>)
[Byline: Editorial Team (eurosurveillance@invs.sante.fr), Eurosurveillance
editorial office.]
